@@citzI am not inferior to YOU.
<p></p>
</br>3 However, I, for my part, would speak to the Almighty himself,
@@citzAnd in arguing with God I would find delight.
<p></p>
</br>4 On the other hand, YOU men are smearers of falsehood;
@@citzAll of YOU are physicians of no value.
<p></p>
</br>5 If only YOU would absolutely keep silent,
@@citzThat it might prove to be wisdom on YOUR part!
<p></p>
</br>6 Hear, please, my counterarguments,
@@citzAnd to the pleadings of my lips pay attention.
<p></p>
</br>7 Will YOU men speak unrighteousness for God himself,
@@citzAnd for him will YOU speak deceit?
<p></p>
</br>8 Will YOU be treating him with partiality,
@@citzOr for the [true] God will YOU contend at law?
<p></p>
</br>9 Would it be good that he sound YOU out?
@@citzOr as one trifles with mortal man will YOU trifle with him?
<p></p>
</br>10 He will positively reprove YOU
@@citzIf in secrecy YOU try to show partiality;
<p></p>
</br>11 Will not his very dignity make YOU start up with fright,
@@citzAnd the very dread of him fall upon YOU?
<p></p>
</br>12 YOUR memorable sayings are proverbs of ashes;
@@citzYOUR shield bosses are as shield bosses of clay.
<p></p>
