@@citzAnd let my declaration be in YOUR ears.
<p></p>
</br>18 Look! Please, I have presented a case of justice;
@@citzI well know that I myself am in the right.
<p></p>
</br>19 Who is the one that will contend with me?
@@citzFor now were I to become silent I should simply expire!
<p></p>
</br>20 Only two things do not do to me;
@@citzIn that case I shall not conceal myself just on your account;
<p></p>
</br>21 Put your own hand far away from upon me,
@@citzAnd the fright of you—may it not terrify me.
<p></p>
</br>22 Either call that I myself may answer;
@@citzOr may I speak, and you return me answer.
<p></p>
