@@citzIn houses in which people will not keep dwelling,
@@citzWhich certainly prove destined for heaps of stones.
<p></p>
</br>29 He will not grow rich and his wealth will not mount up,
@@citzNor will he spread out the acquisition of them over the earth.
<p></p>
</br>30 He will not turn away from darkness;
@@citzHis twig a flame will dry up,
@@citzAnd he will turn aside by a blast of His mouth.
<p></p>
</br>31 Let him put no faith in worthlessness, being led astray,
@@citzFor mere worthlessness will prove to be what he gets in exchange;
<p></p>
</br>32 Before his day will it be fulfilled.
@@citzAnd his shoot itself will certainly not grow luxuriantly.
<p></p>
</br>33 He will thrust away his unripe grapes just like a vine,
@@citzAnd cast off his blossoms just like an olive tree.
<p></p>
</br>34 For the assembly of apostates is sterile,
@@citzAnd fire itself must eat up the tents of bribery.
<p></p>
</br>35 There is a conceiving of trouble and a giving birth to what is hurtful,
@@citzAnd their belly itself prepares deceit.”
