@@citzThat hurtful men have trodden,
<p></p>
</br>16 [Men] who have been snatched away before their time,
@@citzWhose foundation is poured away just as a river,
<p></p>
</br>17 Who are saying to the [true] God: ‘Turn away from us!
@@citzAnd what can the Almighty accomplish against us?’
<p></p>
</br>18 Yet he himself has filled their houses with good things;
@@citzAnd the very counsel of wicked ones has kept far from me.
<p></p>
</br>19 The righteous ones will see and rejoice,
@@citzAnd the innocent one himself will hold them in derision:
<p></p>
</br>20 ‘Truly our antagonists have been effaced;
@@citzAnd what is left of them a fire will certainly eat up.’
<p></p>
</br>21 Acquaint yourself, please, with him, and keep peace;
@@citzThereby good things will come to you.
<p></p>
