@@citzAnd you have made practical wisdom itself known to the multitude!
<p></p>
</br>4 To whom have you told words,
@@citzAnd whose breath has come forth from you?
<p></p>
</br>5 Those impotent in death keep trembling
@@citzBeneath the waters and those residing in them.
<p></p>
</br>6 She´ol is naked in front of him,
@@citzAnd [the place of] destruction has no covering.
<p></p>
</br>7 He is stretching out the north over the empty place,
@@citzHanging the earth upon nothing;
<p></p>
</br>8 Wrapping up the waters in his clouds,
@@citzSo that the cloud mass is not split under them;
<p></p>
</br>9 Enclosing the face of the throne,
@@citzSpreading out over it his cloud.
<p></p>
