@@citzAnd count even all my steps?
<p></p>
</br>5 If I have walked with [men of] untruth,
@@citzAnd my foot hastens to deception,
<p></p>
</br>6 He will weigh me in accurate scales
@@citzAnd God will get to know my integrity.
<p></p>
</br>7 If my stepping deviates from the way,
@@citzOr my heart has walked merely after my eyes,
@@citzOr any defect has stuck in my own palms,
<p></p>
</br>8 Let me sow seed and someone else eat,
@@citzAnd let my own descendants be rooted out.
<p></p>
