@@citzAnd that would be an error for [attention by] the justices.
<p></p>
</br>12 For that is a fire that would eat clear to destruction,
@@citzAnd among all my produce it would take root.
<p></p>
</br>13 If I used to refuse the judgment of my slave man
@@citzOr of my slave girl in their case at law with me,
<p></p>
</br>14 Then what can I do when God rises up?
@@citzAnd when he calls for an accounting, what can I answer him?
<p></p>
