<p></p>
</br>1 So these three men ceased from answering Job, for he was righteous in his own eyes.
</br>2 But the anger of E·li´hu the son of Bar´a·chel the Buz´ite of the family of Ram came to be hot. Against Job his anger blazed over his declaring his own soul righteous rather than God.
</br>3 Also, against his three companions his anger blazed over the fact that they had not found an answer but they proceeded to pronounce God wicked.
</br>4 And E·li´hu himself had waited for Job with words, because they were older than he was in days.
</br>5 And E·li´hu gradually saw that there was no answer in the mouth of the three men, and his anger kept getting hotter.
</br>6 And E·li´hu the son of Bar´a·chel the Buz´ite proceeded to answer and say:
@@citp“Young I am in days
@@citzAnd YOU men are aged.
@@citpThat is why I drew back and was afraid
@@citzTo declare my knowledge to YOU men.
<p></p>
</br>7 I said, ‘Days themselves should speak,
@@citzAnd a multitude of years are what should make wisdom known.’
<p></p>
</br>8 Surely it is the spirit in mortal men
@@citzAnd the breath of the Almighty [that] gives them understanding.
<p></p>
</br>9 It is not those merely abundant in days that prove wise,
@@citzNor those just old that understand judgment.
<p></p>
</br>10 Therefore I said, ‘Do listen to me.
@@citzI shall declare my knowledge, even I.’
<p></p>
</br>11 Look! I have waited for the words of YOU men,
@@citzI kept giving ear to YOUR reasonings,
@@citzUntil YOU could search for words [to say].
<p></p>
</br>12 And to YOU I kept my attention turned,
@@citzAnd here there is no one reproving Job,
@@citzNone of YOU answering his sayings,
<p></p>
</br>13 That YOU may not say, ‘We have found wisdom;
@@citzIt is God that drives him away, not a man.’
<p></p>
</br>14 As he has not arrayed words against me,
@@citzSo with the sayings of YOU men I shall not reply to him.
<p></p>
</br>15 They have been terrified, they have answered no more;
@@citzWords have moved away from them.
<p></p>
</br>16 And I have waited, for they do not continue speaking;
@@citzFor they stood still, they answered no more.
<p></p>
</br>17 I shall give in answer my part, even I;
@@citzI shall declare my knowledge, even I;
<p></p>
</br>18 For I have become full of words;
@@citzSpirit has brought pressure upon me in my belly.
<p></p>
</br>19 Look! My belly is like wine that has no vent;
@@citzLike new skin bottles it wants to burst open.
<p></p>
</br>20 Let me speak that it may be a relief to me.
@@citzI shall open my lips that I may answer.
<p></p>
</br>21 Let me not, please, show partiality to a man;
@@citzAnd on an earthling man I shall not bestow a title;
<p></p>
</br>22 For I certainly do not know how I can bestow a title;
@@citzEasily my Maker would carry me away.
