@@citzAnd knowledge is what my lips do utter sincerely.
<p></p>
</br>4 God’s own spirit made me,
@@citzAnd the Almighty’s own breath proceeded to bring me to life.
<p></p>
</br>5 If you are able, make reply to me,
@@citzArray [words] before me; do take your station.
<p></p>
</br>6 Look! I am to the [true] God just what you are;
@@citzFrom the clay I was shaped, I too.
<p></p>
</br>7 Look! No frightfulness in me will terrify you,
@@citzAnd no pressure by me will be heavy upon you.
<p></p>
